11/05/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Romania and Sweden signed an agreement Monday (10 May) on enhancing bilateral co-operation in fighting terrorism, organised crime, and drugs and human trafficking.
The document was sealed during a meeting in Bucharest between Prime Minister Adrian Nastase and his Swedish counterpart, Goran Persson, who expressed his country's support for the timely conclusion of accession talks between Romania and the EU.
Romania hopes to officially join the Union in 2007.
(Mediafax, Rompres - 10/05/04)
